comment: Butler (CHI) slides his pivot foot after ending his dribble.
Frazier (NOP) makes contact with Butler's (CHI) arm that affects his ability to complete the pass.
Holiday (CHI) sets the screen on Ennis (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Cunningham (NOP) makes incidental contact with Portis (CHI) during rebounding.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was conclusive video evidence that showed that Cunningham (NOP) was the last player to touch the ball prior to it going OOB. The ruling on the court was overturned and Chicago was awarded possession.
Butler (CHI) does not go through the space of Frazier (NOP) on his drive and spin move.
Holiday (CHI) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
RHH shows that Mirotic (CHI) makes contact with Ennis' (NOP) arms during his driving shot attempt.
Ennis (NOP) makes body contact with Butler (CHI) that affects his RSBQ.
Cunningham (NOP) commits a take foul on McDermott (CHI).
Using all available video angles, there is no conclusive video evidence that shows that Ennis (NOP) steps OOB while in possession of the ball.
Douglas (NOP) commits a take foul on McDermott (CHI) prior to the timeout being called.
Cunningham (NOP) commits a take foul on Mirotic (CHI).
Holiday (CHI) makes contact with Hamilton's (NOP) body during his driving shot attempt.

[Incidental or immaterial] Portis (CHI) steps OOB to inbound the ball but then dribbles the ball inbounds. A throw-in which touches the floor on or outside the boundary line is a violation and the ball must be thrown directly inbounds.
